1
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:10,560
Come and eat.

2
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:11,160
Okay.

3
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:12,080
I'm done.

4
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,200
What's wrong with Xiaoyun today?

5
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,880
Look at the time. She's still not up.

6
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,600
I'll go check on her.

7
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,000
Okay.

8
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,810
Xiaoyun, time to get up.

9
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:31,850
Xiaoyun.

10
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:33,520
Xiaoyun!

11
00:01:40,759 --> 00:01:41,640
Estazolam.

12
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:42,610
Xiaoyun!

13
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:43,289
Xiaoyun!

14
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,170
Xiaoyun!

15
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:44,759
Qiming!

16
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,320
Qiming, come here quick!

17
00:01:46,320 --> 00:01:46,800
Coming.

18
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,680
Xiaoyun ate this.

19
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:49,680
What?

20
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,200
Xiaoyun!

21
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:52,560
Xiaoyun!

22
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,120
What should we do?

23
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:56,370
Xiaoyun!

24
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:01,520
What should we do?

25
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:02,320
I'll call 120.

26
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,720
Stay here and watch her.

27
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:04,250
Xiaoyun!

28
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:07,210
Xiaoyun!

29
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,040
Panpan.

30
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:13,840
Why are you here?

31
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,840
Where is your dad?

32
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,730
It's just me.

33
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,720
The neighbors all say

34
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,520
that my dad killed someone because of you that day.

35
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,680
How could that be?

36
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,920
The questions the police asked me that day,

37
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,050
I remember them now.

38
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:27,210
When did Tian Liang go find you?

39
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,640
On the 24th,

40
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:29,920
he hit my dad.

41
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:32,240
Panpan.

42
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,370
Don't worry.

43
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:35,720
I won't let anything happen to your dad.

44
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:37,400
If my dad really did something wrong,

45
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,530
it's all your fault.

46
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:40,760
Panpan.

47
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,970
He hit you again.

48
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,920
I really want to kill him.

49
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,140
I'll go find him right now.

50
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:01,970
On the night of the 24th,

51
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,810
the day of the fight.

52
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:06,720
I killed him.

53
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,080
I admit it.

54
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,410
I came to turn myself in.

55
00:03:12,320 --> 00:03:13,380
You can convict me.

56
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,970
Are you taking the blame for someone else?

57
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,730
Didn't he always abuse you?

58
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,240
Your strength is so different.

59
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,370
How did you kill him?

60
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,880
He drank too much that night,

61
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,079
and couldn't fight back,

62
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:25,960
so I killed him.

63
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,570
I've wanted to kill him for a long time.

64
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,460
Where did you kill him?

65
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:32,640
At home.

66
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:33,720
Where at home?

67
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,400
In the bedroom.

68
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,000
What did you use to kill him?

69
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,200
I... I used a fruit knife.

70
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,040
Which fruit knife?

71
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,720
The one from the kitchen.

72
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,520
Where did you dismember the body? How did you do it?

73
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:41,880
I... I told you, in the bedroom.

74
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,000
How long did it take to dismember the body?

75
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,920
Where did you throw the body?

76
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:44,560
In the bedroom.

77
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,320
Where did you just say you killed him?

78
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,160
In the bathroom.

79
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:46,920
But I've already cleaned it up.

80
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,560
Zhang Yan.

81
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,960
You just said the bedroom.

82
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:56,160
I...

83
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,079
I...

84
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:01,880
How is it, Wang?

85
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,880
Captain Jiang, we still need to examine the scene for a while.

86
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:04,960
But there's a luminol reaction.

87
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,680
However, it's just a small amount.

88
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,200
Okay.

89
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,360
Thanks, Wang.

90
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,440
Good work.

91
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:12,780
A small amount.

92
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,210
This Zhang Yan is indeed lying.

93
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:16,640
She is not the killer.

94
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:18,399
Maybe she's trying to confuse us,

95
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:19,860
and divert our attention.

96
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,000
Then throwing herself into the net like this,

97
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,130
what is her purpose?

98
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,540
To take the blame for that person.

99
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:28,960
Why arrest me?

100
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,860
We need to ask you a few questions.

101
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,460
Is this how you ask questions?

102
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,960
We've already shown you the summons.

103
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:38,020
Please cooperate.

104
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,730
I'm a law-abiding citizen.

105
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,320
Why are you summoning me?

106
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:45,940
We suspect you are involved in a murder case.

107
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,600
You suspect me of murder?

108
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,400
On the nights of July 24th and 25th,

109
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,530
what were you doing?

110
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:56,159
I was with Panpan the whole time.

111
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:58,140
But Li Pan didn't say that.

112
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,840
Do we need to bring Li Pan here

113
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,200
so you can confront her face to face?

114
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,960
I can't remember clearly about those two days.

115
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,440
Let me remind you.

116
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:13,600
During those two days, you and Zhang Yan,

117
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,260
what were you doing together?

118
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:21,680
We...

119
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:25,900
We stayed at the Daheishan Hotel for two nights.

120
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,320
Did you go out during that time?

121
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:28,800
No.

122
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,850
Are you sure?

123
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:30,920
I'm sure.

124
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,500
Every word is true.

125
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:34,180
Do you know Tian Liang?

126
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:35,920
I didn't know him before.

127
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,320
I took Zhang Yan home,

128
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,960
but he thought I was cuckolding him.

129
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,240
Were there any conflicts between you two?

130
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,840
We didn't even know each other before.

131
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,480
How could there be any conflict?

132
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,740
Regarding Tian Liang's disappearance,

133
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:51,159
we hope you can tell us everything you know.

134
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,420
It will be good for you.

135
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,300
I really...

136
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,100
I really don't know anything.

137
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,500
How about this.

138
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,700
We'll give you some more time.

139
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,440
Think about it carefully.

140
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,770
Let's go, Captain Shen.

141
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,020
Captain Jiang.

142
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,970
Look into what he just said.

143
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:11,920
Hey, Xiao Li.

144
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,720
Come over and keep an eye on Li Wei.

145
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,720
Wait for our news.

146
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,850
Zoom in on this footage.

147
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,660
Neither of them had the time to commit the crime,

148
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,460
and they can alibi each other.

149
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:29,380
Who exactly is Zhang Yan helping?

150
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:32,360
Could there be someone else besides Li Wei?

151
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,320
They might have conspired together.

152
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,760
To create an alibi,

153
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,330
they went into the hotel

154
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,640
and came back out.

155
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,659
That's also possible.

156
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,960
Let's go check the room.

157
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:43,400
Okay.

158
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,240
Thank you.

159
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,520
Thank you. You can get back to work.

160
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,980
Thanks for your hard work.

161
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,340
Captain Jiang.

162
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,920
The windowsill is covered in dust.

163
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,040
There's no sign the window was opened.

164
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,640
This window hasn't been opened for a long time.

165
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:34,490
How is it? Can someone get down?

166
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,400
An average person couldn't climb down from this height.

167
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,400
Get up. Let me see.

168
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:46,700
What do you say?

169
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,280
Let's go down and see.

170
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,120
Let's go.

171
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,130
It's so high.

172
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,720
No chance.

173
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,040
Let's go.

174
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:21,940
Hello, sir.

175
00:08:22,120 --> 00:08:22,520
Sir,

176
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:24,460
I'd like to ask you something.

177
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,840
There's a young man living in your neighborhood,

178
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:27,770
a fitness coach,

179
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,000
who always comes back late. Tian Liang.

180
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,960
Did he come back on the 25th

181
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:32,289
or the night of the 26th?

182
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,240
Tian Liang?

183
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,240
That handsome guy,

184
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:35,640
right?

185
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:36,320
Yes.

186
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,720
I didn't see him those two days,

187
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:41,080
but he came back on the night of the 24th.

188
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,340
He left shortly after,

189
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,120
and I haven't seen him since.

190
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,740
Who does he usually hang out with?

191
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:48,720
I'm not exactly sure about that,

192
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:51,780
but he's often picked up and dropped off by luxury cars.

193
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:53,720
Okay,

194
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,770
how about I leave you my number?

195
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,000
I'm a good friend of his,

196
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,240
and I haven't been able to reach him for a long time.

197
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:58,680
Okay.

198
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,480
If you think of anything,

199
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,320
just give me a call.

200
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:02,640
Okay?

201
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:03,170
Alright.

202
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:04,840
Here's my number.

203
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:05,720
Sorry to bother you, sir.

204
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,240
Thank you.

205
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:06,600
No worries.

206
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,000
My surname is Shen.

207
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:07,920
You can just call me Shen.

208
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:08,280
Shen.

209
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:08,840
Thanks.

210
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,560
We'll get going. Thanks for your hard work.

211
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,360
Alright, bye.

212
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,120
Shen.

213
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,200
According to the security guard's testimony,

214
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,600
After Tian Liang went out on the night of the 24th,

215
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,660
he never came back.

216
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:22,020
An eyewitness saw Tian Liang on the 25th.

217
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:24,560
But according to surveillance footage from Daheishan Hotel,

218
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:26,360
Zhang Yan and Li Wei

219
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,760
didn't leave Daheishan Hotel on the night of the 25th,

220
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,360
so they had no time to commit the crime.

221
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:30,920
Indeed.

222
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,320
We can rule them out as suspects.

223
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,800
We're back to square one.

224
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,760
We shouldn't think that way.

225
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,640
After all, ruling out suspects

226
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:39,880
is a good thing for us.

227
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,140
Captain Jiang,

228
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,360
we have to let them go.

229
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,240
Xiaoyun.

230
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,360
Xiaoyun, you're awake.

231
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:13,890
Xiaoyun.

232
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:17,180
What's wrong with you? Why were you so silly?

233
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:18,960
If something really happened to you,

234
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:21,090
did you ever think about your parents?

235
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:22,480
Xiaoyun.

236
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,170
If you have a problem, just tell us.

237
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,520
I'm sorry.

238
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:30,360
I kept you from your work.

239
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:33,120
Don't say that.

240
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:35,250
What exactly happened?

241
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:39,000
Xiaoyun.

242
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,330
Don't be sad.

243
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:41,560
Trust me.

244
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,640
There is no problem that can't be solved.

245
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:44,880
Please stop asking.

246
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,040
Just leave her alone.

247
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,380
I'm going out for a bit.

248
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,320
All right, stop thinking about it.

249
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,450
Get some rest first.

250
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:05,320
What's wrong?

251
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,160
Where are you?

252
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,240
Let's meet tomorrow.

253
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:10,520
Okay.

254
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:19,760
Manager Yu.

255
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:30,960
Isn't this that

256
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:33,420
handsome guy who likes threatening people?

257
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:43,720
What?

258
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:46,380
Couldn't scam money out of Mr. Ye?

259
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,180
It's no use looking for me.

260
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:53,020
Look at this first.

261
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,520
You are so brave.

262
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,800
I need money.

263
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:11,690
Lend me some.

264
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,240
Panpan.

265
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,400
Don't do such silly things in the future.

266
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,400
I am really sorry.

267
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,370
Sorry to cause you trouble.

268
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,720
Fortunately, you didn't cause any trouble this time.

269
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,920
Otherwise, you would really go to jail.

270
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:44,880
Thank you.

271
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:46,480
It's our job.

272
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:48,720
All right.

273
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,060
Go home and rest early.

274
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:50,730
Go ahead.

275
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:51,740
Panpan.

276
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,330
Let's go.

277
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:57,330
Let's go.

278
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:06,320
All right, let's go too.

279
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:07,520
Overtime.

280
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:08,720
Overtime.

281
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,730
I brought the money.

282
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:46,560
Mr. Ye.

283
00:13:47,120 --> 00:13:47,960
That person

284
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,980
has been missing for days.

285
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:51,160
Who?

286
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,570
You didn't watch TV,

287
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,050
or check your phone?

288
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,480
What exactly do you mean?

289
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,040
Give me another 100,000,

290
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,450
